        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 3:08PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 308 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Portland, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Salamonia, College Corner, Boundary City, Liber, Blaine,
Collett, Bluff Point, New Mount Pleasant, Brice, Como, and
Bellfountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
